3.10	B'nai_B'rith_International	B'nai B'rith	B'nai B'rith International (English pronunciation: ; Hebrew: בני ברית, "Sons of the Covenant", the oldest Jewish service organization in the world, is committed to the security and continuity of the Jewish people and the State of Israel and combating antisemitism and bigotry. Its mission is to unite persons of the Jewish faith and to enhance Jewish identity through strengthening Jewish family life; broad-based services for the benefit of senior citizens; and advocacy and action on behalf of Jews throughout the world.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/B%27nai_B%27rith_membership_certificate_1876.jpg/220px-B%27nai_B%27rith_membership_certificate_1876.jpg
